  "text": "One who cuts enough of the hide to make an amulet is liable. And that is when he intends [to cut] the measure of its length and the measure of its width and he cuts with intention, such that it is a type of work. But if he cuts in a ruining way or without intention for its measure, but rather while preoccupied or like one who is playing, he is surely exempt. One who lops off a wing is surely [doing] a subcategory of cutting and is liable. Likewise, one who chisels posts of cedar wood is liable on account of cutting. Likewise, any cutting that a woodworker cuts from wood or a metalsmith from one of the metals is liable on account of cutting. One who takes a wood twig in front of him and snips it to pick his teeth with it or to open a door with it is liable.",
